# Environment Variables
```dotenv
# Environment Variables (example)

#########################
# Frontend (Vite) - Public (safe to expose)
#########################
# Vite exposes only variables prefixed with `VITE_` to the browser.
# These values are safe to include in a local .env for development, but
# never store production secrets in client-side env vars.

# Base URL your frontend will call for backend APIs
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Google OAuth client id (public)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# OPTIONAL: For quick local testing ONLY (DO NOT USE IN PRODUCTION)
# This will expose your Gemini key to the browser â€” prefer server proxy instead.
# VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=


#########################
# Backend (server-only) - Put these in `backend/.env` (DO NOT commit real values)
#########################
# These keys must remain server-side. Commit only this example file.

# MongoDB connection string
MONGO_URI=mongodb://localhost:27017/ai-resume

# JWT secret (use a secure random value in production)
JWT_SECRET=replace_with_secure_random_value

# Server-side AI key for Gemini/OpenAI (server-only)
# The backend should call the AI provider using this key and expose a safe
# API endpoint (e.g. POST /api/ai/generate) for the frontend to use.
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_server_side_gemini_key_here

# URL of the frontend allowed to access the backend
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Backend port
PORT=5000

# Notes:
# - Restart the dev server after changing env files.
# - Add `backend/.env` and top-level `.env` to your `.gitignore` to avoid committing secrets.
# - For production, supply secrets via your hosting platform's environment configuration.
```
